Frequently Asked Questions:

Is real money involved?
No. Million Dollar Club is a strictly simulated environment. It utilizes virtual currency and does not facilitate real-money gambling, nor does it offer real-world prizes or payouts.

My slips aren't settling or updating.
Ensure you have an active internet connection. The app must ping the global sports data feed to verify official match results. Once a match is officially marked as "completed" by the data provider, your open slips will automatically grade and update your balance.

How do I reset my bankroll?
If you go bankrupt or simply want to start fresh, you can reset your account at any time. Navigate to the Settings gear icon located in the top corner of The Vault tab to reset your balance to the default $1,000,000.

Why am I not showing up on the Global Club leaderboard?
The leaderboard utilizes Apple's public CloudKit database. When you first join, it may take a few moments for Apple's servers to globally index your new anonymous profile. Pull to refresh the list to sync your latest rank.

Why aren't all sports or matches available?
To maintain an elite, high-roller environment, we strictly curate our sports roster. We prioritise high-tier, premium global events and verified head-to-head matchups.

